<section xml:id="sec-4-3-first-examples" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
<title>Our First Proof</title>
<introduction>
<p>
    Now that we have our first weapon in hand (the direct proof) let's start to slay our first dragon. 
</p>
<p></p>
<p>
    <alert>Prove: </alert> For all integers <m>x</m>, whenever <m>x</m> is odd then <m>x+1</m> is even.
</p>
<p>Before we begin any proof we sing our song (play-along):</p>
    <p>"What's the <m>{\color{red}{P}}</m>?"</p> 
    <answer>
    <p><m>x</m> is odd</p>
    </answer>
    <p>"What's the <m>{\color{blue}{Q}}</m>?"</p> 
    <answer>
    <p><m>x+1</m> is even</p>
    </answer>
    <p>"What're the definitions?" </p>
    <answer>
    <p>Odd (<xref ref="defn-odd"/>) and even (<xref ref="defn-even"/>)!</p>
    </answer>
    <p>"Now, what to do?"</p> 
    <answer>
    <p>A direct proof! (it is the only method we know so far)</p>
    </answer>
    </introduction>
    
 

